00:48:55.174 --> 00:48:59.697
to actually try to live our lives
in alignment with our own inner wisdom.

00:48:59.744 --> 00:49:02.746
So that means, if we're eating
a regular diet, to move

00:49:02.771 --> 00:49:06.635
toward becoming a vegetarian. If we're
vegetarian, to move toward becoming vegan.

00:49:06.660 --> 00:49:10.861
If we're a vegan, to move toward becoming
a vegan educator or advocate in some way,

00:49:11.045 --> 00:49:15.501
to help spread this idea. Because I think
the more we understand these ideas

00:49:15.684 --> 00:49:19.967
and can bring our lives into alignment
with those ideas, the better chance

00:49:20.124 --> 00:49:24.335
we'll have to actually pass a planet
on to our children that'll be healthy.

00:49:24.436 --> 00:49:27.259
And we'll be able to live healthy
and happy lives ourselves.

00:49:27.363 --> 00:49:30.992
Because the underlying idea
is these universal understandings,

00:49:31.017 --> 00:49:33.872
these universal teachings that
we are all interconnected.

00:49:33.897 --> 00:49:37.931
That all life is interrelated. And that
as we bless others, we will be blessed.

00:49:38.311 --> 00:49:41.792
So does anyone have a question briefly?
I only have a couple minutes here.

00:49:41.910 --> 00:49:44.934
And if you want to ask a question,
please go to this microphone.

00:49:44.981 --> 00:49:48.278
AUDIENCE: Thanks very much for coming
and speaking, and for your work.

00:49:48.560 --> 00:49:50.898
My question is--
there are several parts to it.

00:49:51.046 --> 00:49:57.389
But the basic part is why veganism,
in a sense that why does one have to go

00:49:57.582 --> 00:50:03.438
that far to break free of the lack
of consciousness in the current system?

00:50:04.220 --> 00:50:07.904
So there have been cultures for
thousands of years that hunted animals,

00:50:08.155 --> 00:50:12.499
but did not inflict the kinds of harm that
are caused by modern day agribusiness.

00:50:13.116 --> 00:50:17.584
I've heard of Native American practices
of saying a prayer and asking forgiveness

00:50:17.805 --> 00:50:22.551
from an animal that they had hunted,
which has a degree of consciousness to it.

00:50:22.907 --> 00:50:26.845
Which may not be as nonviolent.
Also wondering if there are some people

00:50:27.019 --> 00:50:30.813
who actually require animal protein
for some reason, for particular reasons?

00:50:32.686 --> 00:50:36.250
People who have chickens at home and get
their eggs, for example.

00:50:36.543 --> 00:50:38.124
It's now part of a larger system.

00:50:38.640 --> 00:50:39.881
WILL TUTTLE: Right.

00:50:39.906 --> 00:50:41.395
A bunch of questions there.

00:50:41.873 --> 00:50:45.624
Most of all of those are addressed
in The World Peace Diet.

00:50:46.094 --> 00:50:49.375
I'm a little concerned on how long
I can answer these questions

00:50:49.400 --> 00:50:51.042
in a short amount of time.

00:50:51.067 --> 00:50:58.043
But basically, I would say
moving toward veganism--

00:50:59.348 --> 00:51:02.953
veganism, to me, is a mentality
of radical inclusion. It's saying

00:51:02.978 --> 00:51:06.953
I'm going to include all living beings in
the sphere of my kindness and compassion.

00:51:06.978 --> 00:51:10.866
And it's also, I think, in many ways,
coming home to our essential true nature

00:51:11.671 --> 00:51:16.877
where I look with eyes that see beings
rather than seeing things.

00:51:17.346 --> 00:51:21.958
And I think anything less than that,
I mean, it's an ideal.

00:51:22.144 --> 00:51:26.526
It's a very high ideal. So I just think
it's the goal to move toward.

00:51:26.739 --> 00:51:31.054
You can be living on the outer level
of a totally vegan life, like no meat,

00:51:31.134 --> 00:51:34.324
no dairy, no eggs, no going to the zoo,
no going to the circus,

00:51:34.349 --> 00:51:36.125
not buying leather, all these things.

00:51:36.150 --> 00:51:39.225
But still, I get angry with people
or I judge them, or whatever.

00:51:39.250 --> 00:51:40.679
That's still not vegan.

00:51:40.849 --> 00:51:46.240
The idea is really, I think, a very
sophisticated level in a sense to evolve

00:51:46.310 --> 00:51:49.145
emotionally, intellectually,
and spiritually to the point

00:51:49.301 --> 00:51:52.858
where we're living a life as much as
possible of kindness and compassion.

00:51:53.301 --> 00:51:58.037
So I think that there maybe have been
other cultures in the past that did

00:51:58.068 --> 00:52:01.179
certain things. I'm not sure.
We don't know what happened on 9/11.

00:52:01.204 --> 00:52:05.487
There's so many arguments about
what happened a 1000, or 10,000 years ago.

00:52:05.963 --> 00:52:08.742
People said that people
ate a lot of meat in the old days,

00:52:08.767 --> 00:52:10.537
and there may be some truth to that.

00:52:10.676 --> 00:52:15.176
A lot of recent research coming out from
non-meat-eating anthropologists is that

00:52:15.364 --> 00:52:17.404
actually cultures that we thought

00:52:17.429 --> 00:52:20.336
were mostly eating meat actually
were not eating mostly meat.

00:52:20.361 --> 00:52:22.790
They were actually eating
mostly plant-based foods.

00:52:22.815 --> 00:52:26.489
And whether there's a necessity
to eat meat, I don't think that's true.

00:52:26.613 --> 00:52:31.842
I've talked a lot of doctors
and researchers who disagree with that.

00:52:31.867 --> 00:52:33.939
That there's any human
being on this planet

00:52:33.964 --> 00:52:35.780
that needs to eat meat for any reason.

00:52:36.343 --> 00:52:38.928
Animals do not contribute any nutrient

00:52:39.176 --> 00:52:41.644
that they didn't get from plants
originally.

00:52:41.669 --> 00:52:47.276
 All the amino acids,
all the vitamins, minerals, fiber,

00:52:49.169 --> 00:52:53.461
essential fatty acids, carbohydrates,
all originates with plants.

00:52:53.486 --> 00:52:56.773
The only two exceptions of that
that we're aware of at this point

00:52:57.022 --> 00:53:00.709
are vitamin D, which is essentially
from the sun, and vitamin B12,

00:53:00.835 --> 00:53:04.610
which is created by bacteria which
normally we'd get in the water.

00:53:04.635 --> 00:53:08.029
But since we chlorinate it and kill
all the bacteria, and perhaps also

00:53:08.054 --> 00:53:14.200
through foods in general. But essentially,
animals don't contribute anything.

00:53:14.386 --> 00:53:16.303
I mean, the animals tend to concentrate

00:53:16.469 --> 00:53:19.532
toxins in their flesh, which we're getting
when we eat them.

00:53:19.580 --> 00:53:23.045
As well as the meta-- the whole chapter
called "The Metaphysical Toxins"

00:53:23.342 --> 00:53:25.615
of eating terror, and fear, and pain.

00:53:26.630 --> 00:53:28.399
I mean, if I'm convinced in my mind

00:53:28.424 --> 00:53:31.602
that I'm not going to be healthy
unless I eat something, then sure.

00:53:31.627 --> 00:53:34.726
I could convince myself
that I was sick so I could tell my mother,

00:53:34.751 --> 00:53:37.277
I don't feel good today.
I don't want to go to school.

00:53:37.302 --> 00:53:40.338
Pretty soon I felt terrible because
I didn't want to lie to her.

00:53:40.391 --> 00:53:43.239
We have to realize that the placebo
effect is very powerful.

00:53:43.264 --> 00:53:45.343
What our minds believe
will be the reality.

00:53:45.368 --> 00:53:47.683
But instead of looking at the past

00:53:47.708 --> 00:53:50.596
to determine our behavior,
why don't we look at the future,

00:53:50.755 --> 00:53:54.913
see the kind of world we want to build,
and move forward, move toward that?

00:53:54.938 --> 00:53:58.212
We can feed everyone on a plant-based die
on a fraction of the land,

00:53:58.507 --> 00:54:00.661
with a fraction of the pollution.
Let's do it.

00:54:00.686 --> 00:54:03.411
Why do we have to look back
and say, well, they did this.

00:54:03.436 --> 00:54:05.831
People look at animals and say,
animals eat meat.

00:54:05.856 --> 00:54:08.511
But we don't say, well,
no animal is building computers.

00:54:08.668 --> 00:54:12.623
But we're building computers. We
don't have to look to these other things.

00:54:13.326 --> 00:54:16.670
The idea is to look ahead
and look what we want to create.

00:54:17.261 --> 00:54:19.636
I have a whole chapter
in The World Peace Diet

00:54:19.661 --> 00:54:22.288
of dealing with
all the rationalizations and objections

00:54:22.313 --> 00:54:24.818
that naturally come up
when people hear these ideas.

00:54:24.843 --> 00:54:28.393
We have certain ones that are told to us.
Jesus ate meat, so it must be OK.

00:54:28.418 --> 00:54:31.574
The Indians were very spiritual.
They ate meat, so it must be good.

00:54:31.599 --> 00:54:34.813
Or plants have feelings, too.
If you eat your carrots, I eat my cow,

00:54:34.838 --> 00:54:36.937
it's the same thing.
They all have feelings.

00:54:36.962 --> 00:54:41.094
There's certain standard objections
that just keep our Sophia repressed.

00:54:42.483 --> 00:54:45.706
and the other thing I'll just mention,
which I think is fascinating.

00:54:45.731 --> 00:54:49.354
Have you heard of Joseph Campbell,
the well-known mythologist? He gave

00:54:49.379 --> 00:54:54.691
a fascinating series of interviews
to Bill Moyer back in the '80s, I think.

00:54:54.942 --> 00:54:59.362
And it was so interesting because I used
to teach college classes in mythology,

00:54:59.387 --> 00:55:01.482
and I read a lot of Campbell's books.

00:55:01.514 --> 00:55:05.076
At one point Bill Moyer asked him,
he said, so, Joseph.

00:55:06.762 --> 00:55:10.404
Human beings seem to be the myth-creating
animal. We create myths.

00:55:10.599 --> 00:55:13.839
We create these stories that tell us how
things happened

00:55:13.864 --> 00:55:17.183
and why they happened, and all of that.
What is the main reason?

00:55:17.208 --> 00:55:19.383
If you could say, what is one main reason

00:55:19.408 --> 00:55:22.864
that human beings create myths,
what would it be?

00:55:22.979 --> 00:55:27.194
And Joseph Campbell said,
the one main reason that human beings

00:55:27.357 --> 00:55:34.249
create myths, these stories that explain
reality, was to rationalize and justify

00:55:34.563 --> 00:55:38.982
killing animals for food.
I went, wow.

00:55:39.404 --> 00:55:44.011
Because this is something that's always
been very hard for us to deal with.

00:55:44.255 --> 00:55:48.465
And we've created an elaborate land of
milk and honey, and Krishna and the Cow,

00:55:48.490 --> 00:55:51.670
and all kinds of things to explain
and rationalize this behavior.

00:55:53.090 --> 00:55:55.439
But I think we can get beyond that level.

00:55:55.464 --> 00:55:57.816
Thank you. Great question.
Really appreciate it.

00:55:57.841 --> 00:56:00.348
